	<!--
	  LSUIElement (v0.21.32, hybrid UX):
	    false = the app behaves like a normal Mac app — Dock icon visible,
	    auto-opens its preferences window on launch, double-clickable from
	    Finder / LaunchPad / Spotlight like any other application.

	  Why this was flipped from true → false in v0.21.32:
	    v0.21.0–0.21.31 ran as LSUIElement=true (menu-bar agent only). Ethan
	    opened v0.21.31 from Finder, saw nothing happen, and asked for the
	    app to behave like a normal app. The previous comment in
	    MacosWidgetsStatsFromWebsiteApp.swift / AppDelegate.swift implied
	    LSUIElement=true was load-bearing for the widget refresh budget /
	    chronod cadence; that turned out to be misleading. The widget
	    refresh benefits come from:
	      (a) the host process staying alive long-term (via LaunchAgent
	          KeepAlive — unaffected by LSUIElement), and
	      (b) sane reload cadence ~30 min (in BackgroundScheduler — also
	          unaffected by LSUIElement).
	    chronod budgets non-foreground / background-window apps and pure
	    LSUIElement agents the same way (~40-70 timeline reloads/day), so
	    flipping LSUIElement off does NOT cost us the widget budget. See
	    LEARNINGS.md (v0.21.32 entry).

	  We KEEP the MenuBarController + NSStatusItem alongside the Dock icon
	  — same hybrid pattern as Bartender, Time Out, iStat Menus.
	-->
	<key>LSUIElement</key>
	<false/>
	<key>NSPrincipalClass</key>
	<string>NSApplication</string>
	<key>SUEnableAutomaticChecks</key>
	<true/>
	<key>SUFeedURL</key>
	<string>https://ethansk.github.io/stats-widget-from-website/appcast.xml</string>
	<key>SUPublicEDKey</key>
